                <span class="expand-content"> The Himalayas, with their steep terrain and seismic activity, are particularly prone to such events, which can have devastating impacts on communities, infrastructure, and ecosystems. Effective DRR strategies in this region can help mitigate the effects of these hazards, safeguard lives, and protect the fragile environment that supports the livelihoods of millions of people. Additionally, by integrating local knowledge and strengthening early warning systems, DRR efforts can enhance resilience and reduce the socio-economic impacts of disasters, ensuring a more sustainable and secure future for Himalayan communities.</span>
